During the course students read and discuss different texts on special educational needs as well as other educational issues and get to know the related vocabulary. The topics include: studying at university, good learning practice, special educational needs, work of a SEN teacher, inclusive education, 21st century skills, etc. Students read scientific texts and make a literature review (autumn term) and an oral presentation (spring term).Objectives/eesmärkid:  To expand students' vocabulary and improve their language skills on B2 language level for working independently with educational and methodological literature of their speciality.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the student: - knows essential vocabulary in the field of special education and general education, and comprehends speciality-related texts; - discusses educational issues within the range of the vocabulary acquired; - summarises and paraphrases educational texts; - compiles and makes an oral presentation on speciality-related literature; - analyses and gives feedback on peers' presentations.
